System profile

Purpose:
- Operating profile for MemoryEndpoints.com as a code-bearing MATM project with local active memory and durable memory pointers.

Verification status: current-state memory; verify against source, tests, reports, and deployment evidence before relying on it.
Memory scope: collaboration model, source authority, quality gates, release gates, and memory architecture.
Public-safe status: safe for source control; contains no credential values.
Update route: update this file when operating model, authority, quality gates, or memory architecture changes.
Source of truth: `workspace.uai`, `AGENTS.md`, `.uai/memory-maintenance.uai`, tests, scripts, and readiness reports.
Next action for agents: align work to this profile before changing source, docs, deployment scripts, or public claims.
Must not expose: raw API keys, bearer tokens, FTP credentials, database passwords, private keys, private handoff payloads, raw one-time keys, private customer data, or deployment credential values.

Operating profile:
- Collaboration model: single maintainer with AI coding agents.
- Target environment: repository handoff plus Python WSGI site and static companion docs.
- Memory architecture: active `.uai` startup suite plus MemoryEndpoints.com MATM durable routes when authenticated.
- Source authority: repository files, current tests, generated reports, live route proof, and explicit human instructions.
- Review posture: public claims require evidence; deployment requires explicit authority and credential access outside memory.
- Tests: run targeted tests for small changes and full local verification before handoff when memory, routes, storage, packaging, or public docs change.
